nutrition:
  calories: 900 kcal
  fat: 50 g
  saturated fat: 24 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 55 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 990 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/garlicky-chicken-with-burrata-and-mushroom-ravioli-656606a3fbf635cc83dfd838
---

Wash and dry produce.

Bring a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4) of salted water to a boil.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry; season all over with @garlic powder{1%tsp}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #large pan{}. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{} to rest.

> While chicken cooks, move on to the next step!

Once water is boiling, add @mushroom ravioli{9%ounce} to #pot{}; cook for ~{1%minute}.

When ravioli has cooked ~{1%minute}, stir in @peas{4%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli are tender and floating to the top, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Reserve ½ cup pasta cooking water, then drain. Return ravioli and peas to pot.

While ravioli and peas cook, zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Return pot with ravioli and peas to stovetop over low heat. Gently stir in @cream sauce base{4%ounce} and juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4). Season with pepper.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until ravioli are coated in a creamy sauce, ~{2-4%minutes}.

> Add splashes of reserved pasta cooking water if sauce seems too thick.

Dice @burrata{4%ounce} into pieces; sprinkle over chicken and ravioli and peas.

Top each serving with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp}; garnish with lemon zest and season with salt and pepper. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.